name: 'Tomorrow is Built Today' exhibition of Black-led self-build
description: Open House of 13 Nubia Way  and oral history exhibition of Europe's largest black-led community self-build for rent  iintiative including archive material and new video. https://sites.gold.ac.uk/inlivingmemory/tomorrow-is-built-today/

name: 80 Charlotte Street
description: This mixed-use scheme completed in June 2020 and comprises 322,000sqft offices, 43,000sqft residential (10,000 sq ft affordable housing), 12,000sqft retail and a new pocket park. It has been designed by leading architects Make.

name: Baitul Amn Mosque
description: Guided Tour of the Mosque. Learn about the purpose of a mosque, listen to the call for prayer, observe worshippers offering prayers, ask any questions, get free souvenirs & literature. Refreshments will be served throughout the day
address: Baitul Amn Mosque, Royal Lane, Uxbridge

name: Brunel Building
description: An architectural landmark, providing a striking addition to the regeneration and vibrancy of Paddington. Providing high quality flexible office space with great natural light, column-free floors, rooftop terraces and a canalside setting.

name: Fore Street Art Trail
description: Enjoy a self guided walking tour of Fore Street to see a wide range of public art including murals and sculptures.
address: Fore Street, Angel Edmonton, Enfield, N18 2UE

name: Immigrant  London
description: Around 35% of Londoners were born outside the UK - itâ€™s  always been a city of immigrants and refugees. Hear the stories of the bankers, the builders, the child refugees and the rogues and their impact on the City for over 2000 years.

name: White Collar Factory
description: Office space that combines the wisdom of well-built industrial spaces with innovative design, sustainable principles, future-proof flexibility and panoramic views. It has achieved BREEAM Outstanding.

name: Yorkton Workshops
description: Yorkton Workshops was restored from a series of dilapidated Victorian stables into a new permanent studio, archive and workshop for Pearson Lloyd. The space also provides a gallery, event space and location available for hire.
